<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Skill Content</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
   <ul class="list-group">
  	<li class="list-group-item">The skill content of the PT MACS is based upon definitions for professional behaviors identified as the Generic Abilities1 and clinical practice as outlined in A Normative Model of Physical Therapist Professional Education2-3 and The Guide to Physical Therapist Practice 4-6. The PT MACS is designed to be used as a method for evaluating clinical performance and as a tool to promote clinical teaching and learning. It identifies skills every student needs to develop in order to be considered entry-level. Clinical Instructors (CIs) and students can also use the PT MACS to collaborate in developing a successful clinical learning experience.</li>
   </ul>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Draft Version 1.0</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
   <ul class="list-group">
  	<li class="list-group-item">Draft version 1.0 of the PT MACS was piloted in 2001 by several member programs of The Consortium. Based on feedback from CIs draft versions 2.0 and 3.0 were created in 2002. Member programs of The Consortium participated in the piloting of the PT MACS between 2001-2003. The first edition of the PT MACS was published in April 2004.
</li>
   </ul>
